               <head>Afghan heresy and genealogy</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary />
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85060381 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh96011772" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_4529-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>Although this work begins by suggesting it is a tafsir, it is in fact a political and historical tract dealing with heresies among the Afghans </p>
                        <p>The work continues by tracing the Afghan genealogy to the Prophet Ibrāhīm via King Ṭālūt (Saul), followed by a chapter on the Yūsufzaʾī, concluding abruptly after the battles of Panipat </p>
                        <p>IOL stamp dated 9 Nov. 1908 </p>
                        <p>The text is only written on the veso side of every folio </p>
                        <p>Carefully boxed and rebound </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian </textLang>
                  </msItem>
